      <!-- Buyer's guide -->
      <article class="legal-prose mt-16">
        <h2>Which MAG setup method should I actually use?</h2>
        <p>
          If you want the shortest possible answer: send us the MAC and use the
          <strong>auto-provisioned Stalker Portal</strong>. It's the fastest, most reliable
          setup and it's what every {site.name} MAG customer uses by default. Only step up to
          <strong>Ministra TV</strong> if you own a MAG 522 or 524 and want the modern EPG and
          catch-up TV interface. The M3U playlist method is a useful fallback if your ISP ever
          blocks the Stalker portal.
        </p>

        <h3>MAG 250 / 254 / 256 owners</h3>
        <p>
          These older MAGs only support the classic Stalker Portal — no Ministra, no M3U app.
          Use the auto-provisioned method: send us the MAC and reboot the portal. Skip 4K
          streams entirely as these boxes cap out at 1080p and struggle with high-bitrate feeds
          on our iptv subscriptions.
        </p>

        <h3>MAG 322 / 324 / 349 owners</h3>
        <p>
          The middle-generation MAGs handle Stalker, Ministra and M3U equally well. This is the
          sweet-spot MAG for a UK <strong>iptv service</strong> — cheap secondhand, still
          responsive, plenty for 1080p sport and film on any <strong>iptv subscription</strong>.
        </p>

        <h3>MAG 420 / 424 / 522 / 524 owners</h3>
        <p>
          Flagship MAGs with 4K HEVC hardware decode. Use Ministra TV to get the full modern
          interface with catch-up TV, then hard-wire Ethernet — the difference over Wi-Fi is
          night and day on 4K UK sport channels included with our
          <strong>iptv subscriptions</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>Try our IPTV UK trial on any MAG box</h2>
        <p>
          Every method on this page works with our <a href="/#pricing">30-day £{site.price} IPTV trial</a> —
          same MAC whitelisting, same UK support on WhatsApp. Your MAC address is registered
          the instant you send it to us on WhatsApp, and one set of credentials from your
          <strong>iptv subscriptions</strong> works across MAG, Fire Stick, Apple TV, Smart TV,
          phone and tablet.
        </p>

        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </article>

